structData.title: Cymbal Validator PRD
structData.body:
Product Requirement Document (PRD)
Project Name: Cymbal Blueprint Validator (CBV)
Version: 1.0
Date: March 2025
Author: Cymbal Product Team
1. Overview
1.1. Executive Summary
Cymbal is developing a SaaS platform, Cymbal Blueprint Validator (CBV), to automate the validation
of architectural blueprints against regional and international building codes. CBV aims to reduce
manual compliance efforts, streamline regulatory approvals, and enhance accuracy in blueprint
validation.
1.2. Business Objectives
- Automate 80% of blueprint compliance checks in the first release.
- Reduce manual review time by 50% within six months of launch.
- Enable integration with existing Cymbal systems (Codex, Horizon, and Atlas).
- Support initial compliance for US (IBC), UK (BS 9999), and EU (Eurocodes).
2. Product Scope
2.1. Problem Statement
Manual blueprint validation is slow, costly, and prone to human error. Existing solutions are
fragmented, requiring architects, engineers, and regulatory bodies to use disparate tools. CBV will
centralize and automate compliance checks, reducing errors and approval times.
2.2. Key Features (MVP)
1. Automated Blueprint Parsing - AI-driven extraction of structural, electrical, and mechanical
elements from CAD files.
2. Building Code Validation - Real-time comparison against predefined compliance rulesets.
3. Error Detection & Reporting - Detailed discrepancy reports with severity classifications.
4. Regulatory Database Integration - Support for US, UK, and EU codes via Codex.

5. Role-Based User Access - Multi-tier access for architects, compliance officers, and reviewers.
6. API Integration - Connectivity with internal Cymbal services (Horizon, Atlas) for automated
submission and compliance tracking.
3. System Architecture & Internal Integrations
3.1. Internal Systems & Codenames
- Codex - Centralized compliance rules database, continuously updated with latest building codes.
- Horizon - Cymbal's cloud-based document repository for blueprint storage and versioning.
- Atlas - Workflow automation engine handling regulatory submission and approval tracking.
4. MVP Scope & Constraints
4.1. Included in MVP
* Parsing of DWG and DXF files for structural compliance.
* Validation against US (IBC), UK (BS 9999), and EU (Eurocodes).
* Error detection and severity classification.
* PDF reports for compliance summaries.
* User dashboard with role-based access.
4.2. Excluded from MVP
X Plumbing and HVAC compliance (Phase 2).
X AI-assisted correction suggestions (Phase 2).
X Support for additional regions beyond US, UK, and EU (Future Release).
5. Success Metrics
- Blueprint Processing Time: < 3 minutes per 50-page blueprint.
- Error Detection Accuracy: > 90% compliance accuracy.
- User Adoption: 100+ firms onboarded within 6 months.
- Regulatory Integration: Full API support for at least 3 government agencies.
6. Timeline & Next Steps
Phase 1: System Design & Prototyping - April 2025
Phase 2: MVP Development - June 2025
Phase 3: Beta Testing (Select Firms) - August 2025
Phase 4: Full Launch - October 2025

structData.title: Cymbal Blueprint PRD
structData.body:
Product Requirement Document (PRD)
Project: Cymbal Home Blueprint Creator (CHBC)
1. Introduction
Cymbal is developing a new SaaS platform called Cymbal Home Blueprint Creator (CHBC) that
allows 
users to design, modify, and export professional-grade home blueprints. This document outlines the 
requirements for the Minimum Viable Product (MVP) and dependencies on internal systems.
2. Objectives
- Provide an intuitive, web-based tool for home blueprint creation.
- Enable blueprint modification using drag-and-drop components.
- Support real-time collaboration for multiple users.
- Generate industry-standard blueprint exports (PDF, DXF, and SVG formats).
- Ensure compliance with regulatory building standards.
3. MVP Definition
The MVP for CHBC will focus on core blueprint creation and export features while leveraging 
existing Cymbal infrastructure. The key MVP features include:
- Web-based 2D blueprint editor with pre-configured home components.
- Real-time collaboration with user access management.
- Basic compliance checks using Cymbal's 'RegCheck' engine.
- Secure storage using Cymbal's 'VaultX' data repository.
- Export functionality to PDF and DXF.
4. Internal Systems & Dependencies
The development of CHBC relies on several existing Cymbal systems:
- 'SkyGrid': User authentication and authorization service.
- 'VaultX': Secure data storage system for blueprints.
- 'RegCheck': Compliance verification engine for regulatory standards.
- 'RenderFlow': High-performance rendering service for blueprint visualization.
- 'PayGate': Subscription and billing integration.

These services must be fully integrated for the MVP to function as intended.
5. Technical Requirements
- The web application must be built using React with a Node.js backend.
- Cloud-hosted on Cymbals AWS infrastructure with Kubernetes orchestration.
- Secure API communication with internal services using OAuth 2.0.
- Frontend must support Chrome, Edge, and Safari.
- Backend must support at least 10,000 concurrent users.
6. Timeline
- Phase 1 (Month 1-2): UI/UX design and backend architecture setup.
- Phase 2 (Month 3-4): Core feature development and API integrations.
- Phase 3 (Month 5-6): Testing, compliance validation, and deployment.
- Phase 4 (Month 7+): Beta release and user feedback integration.
7. Conclusion
This PRD defines the scope, objectives, and MVP requirements for CHBC. The project will 
leverage multiple internal systems and follow a phased approach to development. The successful 
implementation of this SaaS platform will establish Cymbal as a leader in home blueprint solutions.

structData.title: Cymbal Renovate PRD
structData.body:
Product Requirement Document (PRD)
Project Name: Cymbal Renovate
Version: 1.0
Date: March 2025
Author: Cymbal Product Team
1. Overview
Cymbal Renovate is a SaaS platform designed to streamline home renovation projects for homeowners and contractors.
It provides tools for cost estimation, 3D visualizations, project timelines, and workflow management. The service 
integrates with Cymbal's internal systems and third-party tools to ensure a seamless experience from planning to
execution.
2. Objectives
- Enable homeowners to plan renovation projects with accurate cost estimates.
- Provide contractors with a structured workflow and project timeline management.
- Offer 3D visualization tools for project preview and design iteration.
- Integrate with Cymbal's proprietary estimation engine and scheduling system.
- Deliver an MVP within six months with core functionality.
3. MVP Scope
3.1 Core Features
- Project Planning & Budgeting: User-friendly project creation interface, automated cost estimation, budget tracking.
- 3D Visualization & Design: Drag-and-drop interface, AI-generated 3D renderings, PIXEL rendering engine integration.
- Project Timeline & Workflow: Task assignment, timeline visualization, real-time progress tracking.
- Contractor Collaboration: Verified contractor profiles, bidding system, secure messaging.
- Notifications & Reporting: Project updates, weekly reports, customizable alerts.
4. Internal Systems & Integrations
- Cymbal ESTIMATOR: Proprietary cost estimation engine.
- Cymbal PIXEL: 3D visualization and rendering system.
- Cymbal LINK: Verified contractor network database.
- Cymbal ORCHESTRA: Project management and scheduling backend.
- Cymbal VAULT: Secure document storage.
5. User Roles & Permissions

- Homeowner: Create/manage projects, view estimates, approve bids.
- Contractor: Submit proposals, manage tasks, upload invoices.
- Admin: Manage accounts, resolve disputes, adjust settings.
6. Technology Stack
- Frontend: React.js + Next.js
- Backend: Node.js + Express
- Database: PostgreSQL
- 3D Rendering: Three.js + WebGL
- Messaging: Twilio API
- Cloud Storage: AWS S3
7. Success Metrics
- User Adoption: 10,000 sign-ups in Year 1.
- Project Completion Rate: 80% of initiated projects.
- Contractor Engagement: 1,000+ onboarded.
- Revenue Target: $5M in Year 1.
8. Timeline & Milestones
- MVP Feature Lock: Month 1
- Alpha Release: Month 3
- Beta Testing: Month 5
- Public Launch: Month 6
9. Risks & Mitigation
- Regulatory Compliance: Adhere to contractor licensing laws.
- Scalability: Optimize database queries.
- User Adoption: Targeted marketing campaigns.
---
This document serves as the guiding framework for the development and launch of Cymbal Renovate. Further iterations
will refine features based on user feedback and market demands.

structData.title: Cymbal EnergySense PRD
structData.body:
Product Requirement Document (PRD)
Cymbal EnergySense SaaS
1. Overview
1.1 Product Name: Cymbal EnergySense
1.2 Summary:  
Cymbal EnergySense is a SaaS solution designed to analyze home blueprints and provide
homeowners, architects, and builders with energy-efficient design recommendations. 
The service utilizes AI-driven analysis to assess key aspects such as solar panel placement,
insulation improvements, HVAC efficiency, and smart home automation.
1.3 Goals and Objectives:
- Provide automated, AI-driven analysis of home blueprints.
- Deliver actionable recommendations for energy efficiency.
- Support integration with Cymbal's internal systems.
- Establish an MVP with core functionality before expanding features.
2. Stakeholders
- Product Owner: Cymbal Energy Solutions Team
- Engineering Team: Cymbal CoreTech
- Design Team: Cymbal UI/UX
- Business Development: Cymbal GrowthOps
- Customer Support: Cymbal Care
3. Target Users
- Homeowners looking for energy savings.
- Architects & Designers seeking sustainable solutions.
- Builders & Developers aiming to optimize efficiency.
- Energy Consultants advising on green technologies.

4. MVP Scope
4.1 Key Features
1. Blueprint Analysis Engine (Codenamed: ORION)  
   - AI-powered blueprint scanning.
   - Identifies windows, walls, roofing, and electrical layouts.
   - Suggests modifications for energy efficiency.
2. Solar Panel Optimization (Codenamed: HELIOS)  
   - Calculates optimal solar panel placement based on sun exposure.
   - Provides expected energy yield estimates.
3. Insulation & HVAC Efficiency Analysis (Codenamed: AEGIS)  
   - Detects insulation weaknesses and recommends improvements.
   - Analyzes HVAC layout for efficiency gains.
4. Smart Home Automation Recommendations (Codenamed: NEXUS)  
   - Suggests smart thermostats, lighting, and automation enhancements.
   - Integrates with third-party smart home platforms.
5. Report Generation & Recommendations (Codenamed: LUMEN)  
   - Generates a user-friendly report with energy-saving insights.
   - Provides estimated cost savings and efficiency ratings.
5. Technical Requirements
- API Integrations: Connect with third-party solar, HVAC, and automation databases.
- Cloud Infrastructure: Built on Cymbal CloudOps for scalability.
- Security & Compliance: Adheres to data privacy standards (GDPR, CCPA).
- AI Model Training: Utilizes Cymbal DeepLearn Engine for analysis.
6. Success Metrics
- User Engagement: Number of blueprints analyzed.
- Accuracy: % improvement in energy efficiency.
- Adoption Rate: Growth in customer base.
- ROI Impact: Estimated savings per household.

7. Timeline
| Milestone | Timeline |
|-----------|----------|
| MVP Development Start | Q2 2025 |
| Beta Testing | Q4 2025 |
| Public Launch | Q2 2026 |
8. Risks & Dependencies
- Blueprint Format Variability: Need to support multiple file types (PDF, DWG, PNG, etc.).
- AI Model Accuracy: Continuous improvements needed via ML feedback.
- Third-Party API Reliability: Risk of external service downtimes.
- Regulatory Compliance: Must align with global energy efficiency standards.
9. Conclusion
Cymbal EnergySense aims to empower homeowners and industry professionals with AI-driven
insights for energy-efficient home designs. 
By focusing on solar optimization, insulation enhancements, and smart home automation, the
platform will drive sustainability and cost savings at scale.

structData.title: Cymbal PermitFlow PRD
structData.body:
Product Requirements Document (PRD)
Project Name: Cymbal PermitFlow
Document Version: 1.0
Date: March 3, 2025
Author: Cymbal Product Management Team
------------------------------------------
1. Overview
1.1 Summary
Cymbal PermitFlow is a SaaS service designed to streamline the permitting process for construction projects by 
automatically generating a permitting checklist and timeline based on uploaded blueprints.
1.2 Objectives
- Reduce the time required to compile permitting requirements by 80%
- Improve compliance accuracy to 99%
- Provide real-time visibility into the permitting process
1.3 Success Metrics
- User Adoption: 5,000 active users within the first 6 months
- Accuracy: Less than 1% errors in generated checklists
------------------------------------------
2. Functional Requirements
2.1 User Stories
- As a project manager, I want to upload a construction blueprint so that I can receive a customized permitting checklist.
- As a contractor, I want an estimated timeline for each permit so that I can plan my project schedule.
2.2 System Integrations
- Project Blueprint Processing (Codename: ARCHIVE)
- Regulatory Database Connector (Codename: REGCHECK)
- Workflow Automation Engine (Codename: FLOWTIDE)
- Permit Tracking Dashboard (Codename: CLEARVIEW)
------------------------------------------

3. MVP Definition
3.1 Minimum Viable Product (MVP) Scope
Core Features:
1. Blueprint Upload & Processing
2. Automated Permitting Checklist Generation
3. Basic Timeline Estimation
4. Regulatory Data Integration
5. Permit Tracking Dashboard
------------------------------------------
4. Technical Considerations
4.1 Architecture Overview
- Frontend: React-based web application
- Backend: Node.js with Express framework
- Database: PostgreSQL, AWS S3 for file storage
------------------------------------------
5. Risks & Mitigation Strategies
| Risk | Mitigation Strategy |
|------|--------------------|
| Regulatory data inaccuracies | Implement validation layers |
| Integration failures | Develop fallback mechanisms |
| User adoption challenges | Provide onboarding tutorials |
------------------------------------------
6. Timeline & Roadmap
| Phase | Milestone | Estimated Completion |
|-------|----------|------------------|
| Phase 1 | Blueprint processing MVP | Q2 2025 |
| Phase 2 | Checklist & timeline generation | Q3 2025 |
| Phase 3 | Permit tracking & notifications | Q4 2025 |
------------------------------------------
7. Conclusion

Cymbal PermitFlow aims to revolutionize the construction permitting process by reducing manual effort, 
increasing compliance accuracy, and improving project planning.
